<main>
    <section class="page-hero-section">
        <div class="container">
            <h1>Online Coating Weight Gauges</h1>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
        <div class="container spec-sheet-container">
            <div class="breadcrumb">
                <a asp-page="/Products">‹ Back to Products</a>
            </div>

            <div class="spec-sheet-main">
                <div class="spec-sheet-content">
                    <h2>GaugeMaster for Metal Coatings</h2>
                    <p>The GaugeMaster system is a high-performance coating weight gauge featuring low noise and fast response for the most demanding applications on CGL, EGL, and ETL lines. High-power x-ray sources are employed to provide better noise-to-signal ratios for improved control, product quality, and productivity. Differential ion chambers with selected filters ensure high sensitivity and immunity from Compton backscatter effects. A closed loop chiller for cooling the x-ray sources and many other optional features are available. These include split frame scanners, collimated x-ray beams for ridge detection and measuring close to the strip edges, Coil Reports and Archiving.</p>
                    
                    <h3>Key Features</h3>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Coatings Measured:</strong> Single coatings (Zn, Al, Sn, Cr) and Total Coatings (Galfan, Galvalume, Galvanneal).</li>
                        <li><strong>High Performance:</strong> Low noise and fast response for demanding applications.</li>
                        <li><strong>Rugged Hardware:</strong> Measuring heads are mounted on a proven, rugged O-frame design.</li>
                        <li><strong>Flexible Measurement Modes:</strong> Includes Single Point, Continuous Scanning, and Triple Spot modes.</li>
                        <li><strong>Modern Interface:</strong> Features a Main Electronics Cabinet with a Touchscreen Technician's Panel for extensive diagnostics.</li>
                        <li><strong>Reliable OS:</strong> Utilizes Ubuntu (Linux) Real-Time Operating System with separate CPUs for measurements and communications.</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div class="spec-sheet-image">
                    <figure>
                        <div class="spec-image-container aspect-ratio-coating">
                            <picture>
